The TCN is trained in the supervised manner for decreasing the loss function L. There is no data leakage from the future since the output length is equivalent to the input length. Dilated convolutions are present in the TCN to exponentially extend the receptive field, allowing for more past data to be included when forecasting. There is no data leakage from the future data. Equation 5 represents the dilated convolution function. The representation of the dilated convolution with k=â2 and d=â1,2,4,8 is shown in Fig. 3.
